Exposure source. [adapted from (IPCS and IOMC 2004); (van Tongeren et al. 2011); and project meetings].
The origin of substance or a mixture for the purposes of an exposure assessment, in immediate contact with outer surfaces of exposure, to which individuals in the target population may be exposed. Examples are food, drinking water, consumer products, indoor air, outdoor air, dust and soil.
